<br>
Really? Many classes are happy with the spells they are getting. Pretty much everyone woud like more than just 2 spells (myself included, btw, though I do sorta understand why this is all there is), but they generally agree that the spells are good for the level.<br>
<br>
Some very good spells from the new list :<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Temperance</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Cleric, 44). This is Aegolism-lite. Like Aego, it lasts longer the the Symbol spell that is a part of it, and the same duration as the other 2 pieces. It also allows a 44 cleric to buff with a single spell for more than they can currently do until 52. This will be THE Buff spell used by almost every level 44 to 55 Cleric (going with the 3 individual spells instead would give .<br>
<br>
Current max cleric buffs:<br>
Lvl 44 : 638 HP = 162 less than Temperance<br>
Lvl 49 : 775 HP = 25 less<br>
Lvl 52 : 885 HP = 85 more, but the symbol portion has to be refreshed every 54 mins instead of 72. <br>
Lvl 55 : 1000 HP = time to think about retiring Temperance.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Healing Water</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Druid 44)<br>
425 HP for 200 Mana, 4 sec cast time.  2.125 HP/Mana ratio<br>
Compare to Greater Heal : 300 HP for 150 Mana. 2.000 HP/Mana ratio<br>
<br>
Spell will see extensive use from 44 until 51 when it gets replaced by Superior Healing<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Etherial Cleansing</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Paladin 44)<br>
4 tick 100/tick HoT, 150 Mana, 1.5 sec cast. That is 400 HP total for 150 mana. Compare to Greater healing which is the current heal spell for a paladin of this level : 300 HP for 150 mana. EC casts faster, heals more for the same mana, and the only drawback is that it is a HoT. This will be perma-memed by most Paladins until they get Celestial Cleansing at 59.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Light of Life</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Paladin 52)<br>
410 HP for 215 Mana, 1.5 sec cast. Again, the current heal spell for a Paladin of this level is Greater ( 300 for 150, 3.75 cast). Slightly less mana efficient, but the fast cast means the paladin (who is probably tanking) is less likely to be interupted. Will be perma-memed by most Paladins until Touch of Nife at 61. Only spell that might take its place before that is Superior Heal at 57.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Frozen Harpoon</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Wizard 52)<br>
600 Ice Damage for 160 mana. 3.75 HP/Mana<br>
Current best Ice spells at 52 are Lure of Ice (640 HP for 320 Mana, -300 Resist, 2.00 Efficiency) and the venerable Ice Comet (1120 HP for 400 Mana, 2.80 eff). It will serve well until they reach 60 and get Ice Spear of Solist (1200 HP for 300 Mana, Eff = 4.0).<br>
